oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Brass match safe
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Brass match safe with engraved figure of a man on the front. Donor reports that ancestor carried it during "the war"""WA" is inscribed on the back, donor reports that Private William Ary, Co. A, 19th Tenn. Cav., CSA is an ancestor. Although the safe design may be war time, the engraving appears to be post-war.
